# DFS Replication

## Objective

Implement Distributed File System (DFS) Replication to provide redundancy and synchronization of shared resources between multiple servers.

## Environment

- SERVER1
- SERVER2
- Windows Server 2022
- Active Directory Domain

## Tasks Performed

- Installed DFS Replication role services
- Created replication groups
- Added replicated folders
- Configured replication members
- Verified replication topology
- Tested synchronization between servers

## Implementation

A DFS Replication group was configured to synchronize shared data between SERVER1 and SERVER2.

The replication process ensured that file modifications made on one server were automatically propagated to the replication partner.

## Validation

Testing included:

- Creating files on SERVER1 and confirming replication to SERVER2
- Modifying existing files and verifying updates
- Reviewing replication status and health
- Confirming data consistency across both servers

## Benefits

- Improved availability of shared resources
- Reduced risk of data loss
- Simplified management of distributed file shares
- Increased fault tolerance

